MP: Master Panel

EITC: Earned Income Tax Credit

SIRUM: Supporting Initiatives to Redistribute Unused Medicine

ECN: El Camino Nudge (Pre and Post)

Sender: Survey Respondents who completed the survey and then referred another respondent (Respondents who sent out the survey to others).

Recipient: Survey Respondents who had been referred by another respondent to complete the survey (Respondents who received referrals from other respondents).

Our survey respondents can be divided into two groups:

  1. Neither Sender nor Recipient: received surveys directly from us but did not refer others after completing the survey.

  2. Sender and/or Recipient: Received surveys directly from us OR from other respondents, and/or referred other respondents.

How many respondents in each group are willing to take surveys from us in the future?

Sender and/or Recipient

The group can be further divided into three sub-groups:

  1. Senders of Referral Only

  2. Recipients of Referral Only

  3. Both Senders and Recipients of Referral
